<p><strong>Conversion table and conversion factors for the most common temp=
erature units</strong></p><p>If you want to convert Celsius to kelvin, you =
have to add 273 to the Celsius value. When converting from Celsius to Fahre=
nheit, on the other hand, the Celsius value is first multiplied by 1.8 and =
then 32 is added to the result. </p><p>With the WIKA unit converter, you ca=
n, for example, convert Celsius to Fahrenheit, kelvin to Celsius or Fahrenh=
eit to Rankine when dealing with temperatures.</p>

		</div>
